/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/mission-context.md:171:- or can a clever helical or geometric choice suppress enough unwanted
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:5:This is a real chain, not fluff. It does two honest things well: it forces exact bookkeeping early, and it preserves a genuine counterexample search instead of assuming the obstruction must be true. That matters.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:7:The weakness is that it tries to turn a hard object-definition and theorem-calibration problem into a search-and-score problem too early. In this mission, that is dangerous. If "near-closed Tao circuit" has not already survived the Chain 04 invariance audit, then Step 1 just invents a proxy and the rest of the chain optimizes that proxy. Then Step 5 overclaims in both directions: a small-packet partial mimic is treated as a clean kill of the firewall idea, while small-family failure is treated as informative obstruction. Neither inference is earned by the current design.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:9:So the chain is strong as an adversarial stress test and weak as a decisive mission-settling route. Its most likely honest output is a useful diagnostic memo about why small exact packets fail to mimic Tao's circuit, not a clean negative kill and not a theorem-grade positive obstruction.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:19:- The step assumes Tao's mechanism can be approximated continuously. That may be false. Some load-bearing features are structural or one-sided, not "partially present." A packet that gets 80 percent of a score may still miss the one feature that actually matters.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:20:- The score is vulnerable to representation dependence unless Chain 04 has already frozen the invariant object. Phase conventions, packet regrouping, normalization, and helical bookkeeping can all move a candidate's apparent "likeness" without changing the mathematics.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:29:- Restricting the family up front is good protection against p-hacking. But the chosen minimal families may already prejudge failure. Tao's mechanism uses a highly engineered hierarchy of couplings and scales; there is no reason a one-triad or two-triad packet should be the place where a real exact near-circuit, if one exists, first appears.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:30:- The chain says "full conjugate completion," which is necessary but not sufficient. The real burden is exact closure under all forced interactions, not just mirror completion. Once that is imposed honestly, the "small family" may stop being small.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:31:- The search family menu is not evidently exhaustive in the right sense. A shell-bridging packet, two linked triads, and similar templates may miss the one geometric arrangement where unwanted channels partially cancel.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:32:- "What counts as one candidate" is not a minor bookkeeping detail. Continuous symmetries and equivalence classes matter. If this is not normalized carefully, the search either wastes effort on cosmetic variants or buries the real geometry parameters.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:33:- The kill condition is undercalibrated. If every honest family is "already too large for exact bookkeeping," that may mean the construction route is hard, not uninformative. In this mission a hard-to-search exact packet can still be the mathematically relevant one.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:48:Failure mode: Step 3 eliminates the true survivors because they score badly on a static proxy, and promotes algebraically neat packets that later fail for exactly the reasons the proxy could not see.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:54:- The phrase "reduced exact amplitude systems" is the crux. If the candidate is only near-closed, what exactly is being integrated? A truly exact closed packet, or a reduced subsystem obtained by dropping forced modes? If it is the latter, the dynamic test is already compromised.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:60:Failure mode: Step 4 produces attractive trajectories from an already-biased shortlist and then discovers too late that the simulated system was not the honest exact packet problem.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:66:- A single small exact packet that "honestly approximates Tao's logic" is not automatically a clean negative kill of the firewall idea. At most it shows that one obstruction formulation is false for one packet class, unless the near-circuit notion has already been fixed robustly and the candidate survives that exact definition.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:80:### 2. Small-packet success would not prove as much as the chain claims
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:82:The mission asks about an exact no-near-closed-Tao-circuit statement. A tiny packet that partially mimics pump / seed / amplifier / rotor logic does not by itself refute the broader obstruction. It may only show that one naive formulation was too strict.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:84:### 3. Small-packet failure would also not prove as much as the chain hopes
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:86:The chain is explicitly confined to the "smallest" families. That is useful for bounded exploration and weak as evidence about the true landscape. If the obstruction fails only in a slightly larger or more asymmetric packet, this chain will miss it and still be tempted to package the miss as structure.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/attacks/chain-03.md:106:- exact closure bookkeeping,
