/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner.md:19:Central premise: even if some desired channels can be matched, exact Fourier/helical closure plus mirror-mode bookkeeping forces enough extra interactions that any honest Tao-like subsystem leaks a quantifiable amount of activity outside the five target roles.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner.md:23:Central premise: the obstruction might be false. The fastest honest kill is to search directly for the best exact NS or helical packet that approximates Tao's logic and see whether it survives exact coupling accounting.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner.md:27:Central premise: the whole mission may fail at the object-definition level. If every reasonable definition of near-closure is unstable under phase choice, packetization, scaling, or conjugate completion, the right result is a sharp definitional kill rather than a fake theorem program.
