/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner-chains/chain-02.md:60:Action: search the allowed geometry families for worst-case leakage, including near-degenerate or specially aligned helical configurations.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner-chains/chain-02.md:72:Action: if the infimum leakage stays positive, formulate the cleanest no-near-closure statement available, naming the packet class, leakage functional, and bound.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/refined/chain-02.md:5:This branch is only live after one stable notion of a near-closed Tao circuit has been fixed. Given that frozen object, the question is whether exact Navier-Stokes forces a uniformly nontrivial off-circuit transfer on an explicit packet class, or whether an adversarial family can drive that transfer to zero while preserving the intended Tao-role logic over a stated activation window.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/refined/chain-02.md:11:- a class-conditional lower bound showing that every exact packet in a specified symmetry-normalized family realizing the target Tao-role channels incurs at least a fixed amount of off-circuit transfer in one stated observable over one stated window; or
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/refined/chain-02.md:17:This chain no longer treats leakage as a freely chosen ratio, no longer assumes minimal finite packets are decisive, and no longer jumps from closure bookkeeping to theorem rhetoric. It is a downstream quantitative test on one frozen near-closure definition, one packet class, one observable, and one declared time window.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/refined/chain-02.md:21:### Step 1 - Import the frozen theorem object and admissible packet class
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/refined/chain-02.md:25:Action: adopt one near-closure definition that is already stable under packetization, normalization, conjugate completion, and basis bookkeeping. If no such object has been supplied by the definition-audit branch, stop immediately.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/refined/chain-02.md:27:Action: specify one packet class to test, including allowed role assignment, symmetry completion, redundancy rules, tail rules if any, shell geometry limits, and whether finitely supported packets are only a calibration subclass or the full theorem class.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/refined/chain-02.md:29:Expected output: an object sheet fixing the near-closure metric, bookkeeping stack, admissible packet family, and comparison window.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/refined/chain-02.md:39:Action: define exactly how the observable is normalized across packet size, amplitude scaling, initial spectator amplitudes, and role assignment. Reject observables that can be changed substantially by harmless regrouping or bookkeeping choices.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/refined/chain-02.md:43:Kill condition: if no observable is both invariant enough and dynamical enough to compare packet realizations honestly, stop and record a leakage-definition obstruction.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/refined/chain-02.md:45:### Step 3 - Build a parameterized forced-spectator ledger for the full packet class
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/refined/chain-02.md:49:Action: compute the forced on-class and off-class interactions for the chosen packet family, with geometry, helicity, conjugate completion, and allowed redundancy included from the start rather than as a late stress test.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/refined/chain-02.md:51:Action: use minimal packets only as calibration examples. Any claimed obstruction must survive extension to the declared family, including small tails if those are allowed by Step 1.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/refined/chain-02.md:55:Kill condition: if the packet family itself is not coherent under the chosen bookkeeping stack, stop and report class-definition failure.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/refined/chain-02.md:61:Action: derive lower-bound candidates only through identities that feed the Step 2 observable on the Step 1 time window. Track explicitly where phase cancellation, helical signs, delayed buildup, and pre-existing spectator amplitudes enter.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/refined/chain-02.md:73:Action: if a positive infimum survives, state it with exact hypotheses: packet class, near-closure metric, observable, time window, and bound. Restricted packet-class theorems are acceptable if their scope is explicit.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/refined/chain-02.md:77:Action: if neither side is earned, state precisely why the leakage route fails, for example: invariant observable unavailable, cancellations destroy coercivity, or packet-class dependence prevents theorem scope.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-02.md:5:The attacker is mostly right. The original chain points at a real mission-aligned pressure point: exact Navier-Stokes may realize some desired Tao-role channels while still failing to isolate them. But the chain treated "leakage" as if it could be chosen by bookkeeping, delayed the geometry and helicity adversary too long, and moved too quickly from forced couplings to a dynamical obstruction claim.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-02.md:7:The right repair is not to discard the chain. It is to narrow it into a downstream quantitative test that only starts after a stable near-closure object is fixed, uses one invariant dynamical observable, treats minimal packets as calibration rather than theorem scope, and allows an honest middle outcome where the leakage route itself fails to produce a class-uniform theorem.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-02.md:15:This is the load-bearing criticism. The original Step 1 acted as if one could simply choose a leakage functional and closure rule, but this mission already identified object-definition instability as a first-order risk. Also, exact Fourier support closure, helical triad bookkeeping, and conjugate completion are not interchangeable options on one level. The refined chain should therefore begin only after one stable near-closure object has been frozen, ideally by Chain 04.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-02.md:17:### 2. The focus on smallest candidate packets risks small-packet bias and overcounting
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-02.md:21:The attacker is right that a theorem proved only for minimal packets may miss redundancy, distributed role assignment, or small tails. The attacker is also right that a forced ledger can overstate importance if it counts channels that are dynamically negligible or cancellation-prone. But starting with minimal packets is still a reasonable calibration move. The defect was not using them first; it was letting them implicitly define the whole theorem class.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-02.md:33:The core objection is correct: geometry and helicity choices determine the ledger itself, so they cannot be postponed until after a lower-bound worksheet is built. Those adversarial degrees of freedom must be present when the packet class and observable are fixed. But the attacker goes too far in implying that collapse on a special family always means the theorem object is wrong. A lower bound on an explicit restricted class can still be mathematically real and mission-useful if its scope is stated honestly.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-02.md:39:The original finish allowed only two clean endings: positive leakage bound or explicit vanishing-leakage family. That misses the likely middle case where the route fails because the observable is not invariant enough, the cancellations destroy coercivity, or the bound depends too strongly on packet-class choices. The refined chain should permit that meta-obstruction as a presentable output.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-02.md:53:3. It treats minimal packets as calibration only and requires the claimed result to survive on an explicit packet family with stated redundancy or tail rules.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-02.md:63:- The probability is not higher because the hard step remains genuinely hard: turning forced spectators into a class-uniform dynamical lower bound under adversarial geometry, helicity, phases, and packet redundancy.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/judgments/chain-02.md:64:- The most plausible success mode is not a universal no-near-closure theorem, but either a restricted-class leakage bound or a clean diagnosis of why the leakage program cannot support such a theorem without stronger hypotheses.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/selected/chain-01.md:5:The prior mission already identified that "exact-NS circuit non-isolability" failed because it was not yet a concrete object. The cleanest early kill is to test whether any precise definition of a near-closed Tao circuit remains stable under the unavoidable exact symmetries and bookkeeping choices of Fourier/helical NS.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/selected/chain-01.md:12:- a definition-level obstruction memo proving that every plausible definition is too unstable, too representation-dependent, or too unconstrained to support a theorem test.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/selected/chain-01.md:29:Action: make each definition explicit about support, normalization, time window, and admissible spectator size.
