+# Exploration 001 Report
+
+## Goal
+
+Separate Tao-circuit features that are genuinely load-bearing for this mission
+branch from features that are merely convenient packaging, while keeping clear
+boundaries between:
+
+- Tao's internal averaged/shell mechanism;
+- exact-NS mismatch claims inherited from the prior Atlas reconstruction;
+- and this branch's Step-1 scope-lock commitments.
+
+## Method
+
+- Read the required source anchors first.
+- Extract the literal Tao mechanism from the anatomy reports.
+- Separate direct Tao-mechanism facts from later branch-policy items such as
+  leakage language and canonicalization.
+- Classify each target feature as `essential`, `dispensable`, or
+  `open but load-bearing`.
+- Mark major conclusions as `[VERIFIED]`, `[INFERRED]`, or `[PROPOSED]`.
+- Record dead ends rather than forcing certainty where the inherited record is
+  intentionally incomplete.
+
